title: Russia Says Google Has “Violated Competition Rules” With Android, Yandex Stock Jumps - newsR
text: Back in February, the “Google of Russia”, Yandex, filed an antitrust complaint with Russia’s watchdog agency (FAS) over Google’s leverage with what comes pre-installed on Android. Specifically, the fact that Google is the default search engine rubbed Yandex the wrong way. See, Yandex has a 60% search hold overall, but Android phones account for 86% of all smartphones… Read More »
